I"q9<p>Lets start this article about altcoin wallets right off with the obligatory reminder.</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>For hodlers: <strong>It is not a good idea to keep untraded cryptocurrency on an exchange.</strong></p>
</blockquote>

<p>Exchanges hold larger amounts of crypto than personal wallets and therefore are more targeted by cyber criminals.</p>

<ul>
  <li>Read about the <a href="https://www.altcointrading.net/bitfinex-tether-transparency/">Tether hack in 2017</a></li>
  <li>Or about the <a href="https://www.altcointrading.net/dao-hack/">DAO hack in 2016</a></li>
  <li>Or about the <a href="https://www.altcointrading.net/finexening/">Bitfinex hack in 2016</a></li>
</ul>

<blockquote>
  <p>For traders: <strong>It is also not a good idea to send coins from one exchange to another.</strong></p>
</blockquote>

<p>Exchange transaction systems are a blackbox, especially with high-tech altcoins like Ethereum that support sending triggered by a smart contract.</p>

<p>An altcoin wallet will receive such transaction, but an <a href="https://www.altcointrading.net/bitifinex-eats-your-eth/">exchange which has built in security mechanisms to avoid network spam might not</a>. You can go spend months dealing with customer support to retrieve your funds, sure. But I guess you have better things to do.</p>

<p><strong>And now, quick TLDR for those who don’t want to get paralyzed by too many options:</strong></p>

<h3 id="your-best-bet-in-terms-of-altcoin-storage">Your best bet in terms of altcoin storage</h3>

<p><strong>Everyone’s Favorite Altcoin Wallet</strong>: <a href="https://bit.ly/lnx_at_altcoinwallets">The Ledger Nano X</a></p>

<p>Ledger Nano X is particularly good for altcoin traders because it has larger memory capacity. That means a single device can house private keys of many more cryptocurrencies than Ledger Nano S.</p>

<p>Ledger wallets were the pioneers of supporting altcoins, and you will find most cryptos are supported unless they are really brand new.</p>

<ul>
  <li>Some of the supported cryptocurrencies: Bitcoin, Ethereum, IOTA, Ethereum Classic, Dogecoin, Litecoin, Zcash, Dash, Ripple, Stratis and <strong>all ERC20 compliant Ethereum tokens</strong>.</li>
</ul>

<p>Since 2019, all Ledger wallets come with a secure app suite called Ledger Live.</p>

<p><em>The Nano X is often offered in discount bundles and recently Ledger also started experimenting with discount codes. We keep all such offers throughout the year on our Black Friday page.</em></p>

<p>
<a class="btn" href="https://bit.ly/lnx_at_altcoinwallets">Get Ledger Nano X</a>
&nbsp;
<a class="btn" href="/blackfriday/">Check Year-Long BlackFriday Offers</a>
</p>

<h3 id="your-most-easy-to-use-altcoin-wallet">Your most easy-to-use altcoin wallet</h3>

<p>If you only need to store <strong>BTC, ETH and XLM</strong>, the best smartphone app for you in 2020 the <strong>blockchain.com</strong> wallet (formerly blockchain.info).</p>

<ul>
  <li>The smartphone app can be unlocked with PIN or fingerprint, if your device supports that.</li>
  <li>Blockchain.com still provides the web interface, too. It has multiple levels of second and third factor authentication and options to only whitelist access from certain locations.</li>
</ul>

<p>Be careful though: The <code class="highlighter-rouge">blockchain.com</code> wallet is the favorite target of imposter attacks. Always double check you are downloading the app from developer company <strong>Blockchain Luxembourg SARL</strong>.</p>

<p><strong>If you need more altcoins</strong> or if you prefer a standalone app for phones and desktop with no website interface, go with <a href="https://www.exodus.io/">Exodus.io</a>.</p>

<ul>
  <li>Exodus has been adding easy support of popular ERC20 tokens as well as selected stablecoins.</li>
  <li>If Exodus and Jaxx used to be competitors, Exodus won.</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Now for the detailed stuff.</strong></p>

