<h4 id="trezor-wallet-for-altcoins">Trezor wallet for Altcoins</h4>

<p>Trezor utilizes similar system as Ledger Wallet. There is a set of native apps, you are able to manage several cryptocurrency wallets from a web app after unlocking your access with your PIN.</p>

<p>Trezor is not as popular as ledger because it’s more expensive and less user-friendly.</p>

<ul>
  <li>TREZOR supports natively: <strong>BTC, ETH, DASH, LTC and ZCASH</strong>.</li>
  <li>Via 3rd party private key management: <strong>Any ERC20 token</strong> via MyEtherWallet.</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>On Reddit:</strong></p>

<ul>
  <li>Subreddit - <a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/trezor">r/TREZOR</a></li>
  <li>People - <a href="https://www.reddit.com/u/slush0">u/slush0</a>, <a href="https://www.reddit.com/u/stickac">u/stickac</a></li>
</ul>

<p> </p>

<h3 id="electrum-forks">Electrum Forks</h3>

<p>While Electrum for Bitcoin (<a href="https://electrum.org/#home">https://electrum.org/</a>) is a safe option, you should be careful with Electrum for altcoins. The altcoin versions of Electrum were not developed by the same author as the original Electrum.</p>

<p>They are just forks - the Electrum code is open-sourced.</p>

<p>Some of them <em>can</em> be malicious or forked from an old version of Electrum that has a vulnerability:</p>

<p><a target="_blank" href="https://res.cloudinary.com/atnetcloud/image/upload/c_scale,w_700/c_crop,g_north,h_360,w_700/v1588053117/atnet/altcoin-wallets/Screen_Shot_2020-04-28_at_12.37.36_cqbzj7.jpg" title="AltcoinTrading.NET - "><figure class="border"><amp-img itemprop="image" src="https://res.cloudinary.com/atnetcloud/image/upload/c_scale,w_700/c_crop,g_north,h_360,w_700/v1588053117/atnet/altcoin-wallets/Screen_Shot_2020-04-28_at_12.37.36_cqbzj7.jpg" alt="" title="AltcoinTrading.NET - " layout="responsive" width="700px" height="360px"></amp-img></figure></a></p>

<p>You should only use an Electrum fork if you are able to check its codebase and confirm the code is not malicious.</p>

<p>These two Electrum forks have been quite popular:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Electrum for Litecoin - <a href="https://electrum-ltc.org/">https://electrum-ltc.org/</a></li>
  <li>Electrum for Dash - <a href="https://www.dash.org/downloads">https://www.dash.org/downloads</a></li>
</ul>

<h3 id="best-monero-wallet">Best Monero Wallet</h3>

<p><a target="_blank" href="https://res.cloudinary.com/atnetcloud/image/upload/c_scale,h_360/c_crop,g_west,h_360,w_700/v1588057688/atnet/altcoin-wallets/Screen_Shot_2020-04-28_at_14.07.35_hp3g8r.jpg" title="AltcoinTrading.NET - "><figure class="border"><amp-img itemprop="image" src="https://res.cloudinary.com/atnetcloud/image/upload/c_scale,h_360/c_crop,g_west,h_360,w_700/v1588057688/atnet/altcoin-wallets/Screen_Shot_2020-04-28_at_14.07.35_hp3g8r.jpg" alt="" title="AltcoinTrading.NET - " layout="responsive" width="700px" height="360px"></amp-img></figure></a></p>

<h4 id="mymonero-lightweight-wallet">MyMonero Lightweight Wallet</h4>

<p><strong><a href="https://mymonero.com/#/">MyMonero</a></strong></p>

<p>MyMonero has been long endorsed on the Monero’s official website (getmonero.com).</p>

<p>It has been around for years, originally only available as a web wallet. In 2020 you get the <a href="https://wallet.mymonero.com/">monero web wallet</a> and a <a href="https://mymonero.com/">desktop/smartphone app</a>.</p>

<p>The wallet is super simple. No sign up, just a private key generation. The key is not stored on the server, you are the only person who has it.</p>

<h3 id="best-multi-coin-wallets">Best Multi-Coin Wallets</h3>

<h4 id="exodus-multicoin-wallet">Exodus Multicoin Wallet</h4>

<p><a target="_blank" href="https://res.cloudinary.com/atnetcloud/image/upload/c_scale,h_360/c_crop,h_360,w_700/v1588058978/atnet/altcoin-wallets/Screen_Shot_2020-04-28_at_14.18.06_owggbk.jpg" title="AltcoinTrading.NET - "><figure class="border"><amp-img itemprop="image" src="https://res.cloudinary.com/atnetcloud/image/upload/c_scale,h_360/c_crop,h_360,w_700/v1588058978/atnet/altcoin-wallets/Screen_Shot_2020-04-28_at_14.18.06_owggbk.jpg" alt="" title="AltcoinTrading.NET - " layout="responsive" width="700px" height="360px"></amp-img></figure></a></p>

<p><a href="https://www.exodus.io/">https://www.exodus.io/</a></p>

<p>Exodus was the first multicoin wallet to integrate an altcoin exchange right inside the app.</p>

<p>It’s currently your best option for a multicoin wallet: The amount of supported coins is the largest, the support is great, you get a status page in case your app gets sluggish and the app also integrates with TREZOR hardware wallets.</p>

<p>Exodus wallet is super user-friendly and great for the beginners:</p>
<ul>
  <li>You launch the wallet as any other app, no user sign up.</li>
  <li>As there are over 100 altcoins supported, you need to enable wallet functionality for any coin you want to store.</li>
  <li>Wallets are automatically generated for you. No seed handling etc.</li>
  <li>To see your private keys (seed), you need to run backup. The <a href="https://support.exodus.io/article/41-how-do-i-backup-my-exodus-wallet">Exodus backup option</a> is only unlocked after you make a deposit though, as for an empty wallet you don’t need a backup.</li>
  <li>At the same time, the only owner of your private keys is you.</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Supported coins:</strong> BTC, ETH, ERC20 tokens, Tezos, EOS, XRP, TRX… <strong>= 110 cryptoassets in total</strong></p>

<h4 id="jaxx-multicoin-wallet">Jaxx Multicoin Wallet</h4>

<p><a target="_blank" href="https://res.cloudinary.com/atnetcloud/image/upload/c_scale,w_700/c_crop,h_360,w_700/v1588058183/atnet/altcoin-wallets/Screen_Shot_2020-04-28_at_14.16.02_scvbmp.jpg" title="AltcoinTrading.NET - "><figure class="border"><amp-img itemprop="image" src="https://res.cloudinary.com/atnetcloud/image/upload/c_scale,w_700/c_crop,h_360,w_700/v1588058183/atnet/altcoin-wallets/Screen_Shot_2020-04-28_at_14.16.02_scvbmp.jpg" alt="" title="AltcoinTrading.NET - " layout="responsive" width="700px" height="360px"></amp-img></figure></a></p>

<p><a href="https://www.jaxx.io/">https://www.jaxx.io/</a></p>

<p>Still one of the most popular multicoin wallets these days is <a href="https://jaxx.io/support.html">Jaxx</a>. It is available as browser extension, desktop app and mobile app - although the choice of supported coins differs.</p>

<p>Jaxx wallet is super user-friendly and great for the beginners:</p>
<ul>
  <li>You launch the wallet as any other app, no user sign up.</li>
  <li>Wallets are automatically generated for you. No seed handling etc.</li>
  <li>To see your private keys (seed), you need to run backup. You will find this option under settings on the right hand side.</li>
  <li>At the same time, the only owner of your private keys is you.</li>
</ul>

<p>Since Jaxx 1.2 you get <a href="https://shapeshift.io/">Shapeshift</a> integrated within the wallet.</p>

<p><strong>Supported coins:</strong> BTC, ETH, ERC20 via MyEtherWallet, ETC, DASH, LTC, REP, RSK, ZEC… <strong>= 90 cryptoassets in total</strong></p>

<h3 id="web-based-multi-altcoin-wallets">Web Based Multi-Altcoin Wallets</h3>

<p>Most web-based wallets, the private keys are stored by a third party. You should not consider these as a safe altcoin storage.</p>

<p>Opt for blockchain.com or one of the multicoin wallets above for a good ratio of convenience and security.</p>
